new%20doctrine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20had%20been%20stretched%20when%20fighting%20at%20the%20same%20time%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Iraq.%20It%20prompted%20a%202009%20rethink%20of%20US%20military%20doctrine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2009%2F03%2F15%2Fwashington%2F15military.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20President%20Barack%20Obama%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20rubber-stamped%20by%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20later%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20winning%20two%20wars%2C%20it's%20now%20committed%20to%20being%20able%20to%20win%20against%20one%20major%20adversary%20such%20as%20China%2C%20and%20to%20present%20a%20serious%20deterrent%20to%20attacks%20from%20other%20enemies%2C%20Cohen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F3202438%2Fdod-releases-national-defense-strategy-missile-defense-nuclear-posture-reviews%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPentagon's%202022%20US%20National%20Defense%20Strategy%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20most%20recent%2C%20commits%20the%20US%20to%20being%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bprevail%20in%20conflict%26quot%3B%20yet%20still%20%26quot%3Bdeter%20opportunistic%20aggression%20elsewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20planning%20for%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20new%20world%20war%2C%20the%20US%20must%20look%20at%20the%20global%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20long%20relied%20on%20its%20enemies%20being%20divided%2C%20and%20unlikely%20to%20join%20forces%20to%20attack%20the%20US%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20and%20other%20US%20adversaries%20are%20drawing%20closer%20together%2C%20sharing%20weapons%20technology%20and%20drawing%20up%20new%20alliances%2C%20magnifying%20their%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20worst-case%20scenario%20in%20which%20various%20nation-state%20adversaries%20of%20the%20US%20attacked%20simult