0former%20company%20president%20Greg%20Brockman%20followed%20Altman%20out%20of%20OpenAI%20and%20into%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20Monday%2C%20almost%20all%20employees%20at%20OpenAI%20had%20signed%20a%20letter%20threatening%20to%20quit%20unless%20Altman%20returned%20and%20the%20board%20resigned.%20Just%20a%20day%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-return-openai-ceo-2023-11%3F_gl%3D1*kas3ty*_ga*Nzg4MjgyNjAxLjE2NzM2MTAyNDA.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMDY1NjM4NC43NjkuMS4xNzAwNjU2Mzg0LjYwLjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAltman%20was%20back%20as%20CEO%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20board%20was%20largely%20replaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unprecedented%20mess%20has%20left%20commentators%20wondering%20what%20could%20have%20caused%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20AI%20companies%20to%20shoot%20itself%20in%20the%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vague%20language%20and%20general%20lack%20of%20explanation%20provided%20by%20the%20board%20%E2%80%94%20even%20to%20its%20most%20important%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20has%20let%20speculation%20run%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20may%20never%20know%20why%20Altman%20was%20ousted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20million%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-20%2Fsam-altman-openai-latest-inside-his-shock-firing-by-the-board%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2486%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20dollar%20question%20on%20everyone's%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20was%20Sam%20Altman%20suddenly%20fired%20as%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board's%20initial%20explanation%20included%20a%20scathing%20statement%20about%20Altman's%20communication.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fblog%2Fopenai-announces-leadership-transition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20blogpost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20board%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Altman's%20departure%20follows%20a%20deliberative%20review%20p