0OpenAI's%20chief%20scientist%20who%20was%20rumored%20to%20play%20a%20central%20role%20in%20Sam%20Altman's%20ousting%2C%20was%20committed%20to%20AI%20safety.%20Sutskever%20and%20Altman%20often%20clashed%20over%20differences%20around%20ways%20to%20reduce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-18%2Fopenai-altman-ouster-followed-debates-between-altman-board%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI's%20potential%20harm%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20humanity%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Altman%20has%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20AI%2C%20he%20has%20also%20been%20pushing%20the%20commercialization%20of%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20possibly%20at%20a%20pace%20the%20safety-conscious%20board%20was%20not%20OK%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20appeared%20to%20push%20back%20on%20the%20speculation%20around%20AI%20safety's%20role%20in%20Altman's%20departure.%20Employees%20were%20told%20over%20the%20weekend%20his%20dismissal%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20%26quot%3Bmalfeasance%20or%20anything%20related%20to%20our%20financial%2C%20business%2C%20safety%20or%20security%2Fprivacy%20practice%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F18%2Ftechnology%2Fopen-ai-sam-altman-what-happened.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20viewed%20by%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWill%20OpenAI%20change%20its%20complex%20structure%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20popular%20theories%20for%20Altman's%20ousting%20is%20that%20tensions%20between%20the%20nonprofit%20board%20and%20the%20for-profit%20arm%20of%20OpenAI%20finally%20came%20to%20a%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nonprofit%20board%2C%20which%20included%20chief%20scientist%20Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20ultimately%20had%20the%20power%20to%20fire%20Altman%20because%20of%20the%20company's%20unusual%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESources%20inside%20OpenAI%20at%20the%20time%20told%20The%20Atlantic%20that%20the%20release%20of%20ChatGPT%20had%20highlighted%20underlying%20ideological%20conflicts%20between%20the%20nonprofit%20board%20and%20the%20for-profit%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPressure%20to%20commercialize%20the%20chatbot%20created%20divisions%20among%20leadership%2C%20they%20said.%20While%20OpenAI's%20safety%20teams%20wanted%20to%20slow%20things%20down%2C%20the%20product%20teams%20pushed%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20hype.%20The%20launch%20of%20further%20products%2C%20including%20a%20premium%20tier%20of%20ChatGPT%20powered%20by%20GPT-4%2C%20only%20served%20to%20exasperate%20the%20issues%2C%20sources%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20board%20had%20been%20all%20but%20replaced%2C%20with%20only%20Quora%20CEO%20Adam%20D'Angelo%20holding%20a%20seat%20on%20the%20new%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20Microsoft%20thinking%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20ousted%20Altman%20without%20consulting%20its%20lead%20investor%2C%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20reportedly%20didn't%20go%20down%20well%20with%20its%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella.%20After%20leading%20talks%20to%20try%20and%20get%20Altman%20reinstated%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20Nadella%20later%20hired%20him%20and%20Brockman%20to%20head%20up%20an%20AI%20team%20at%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20has%20been%20clear%20that%20he%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20caught%20off-guard%20about%20major%20leadership%20shakeups%20at%20OpenAI%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20appearing%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Fepisode%2F4i4lKsKevNSGEUnuu7Jzn6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epodcast%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ewith%20journalist%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%20Nadella%20said%20OpenAI%20should've%20consulted%20Microsoft%20before%20firing%20the%20former%20CEO.%20He%20added%20that%20it%20would've%20been%20the%20%26quot%3Bvery%20least%26quot%3B%20the%20board%20could%20have%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20seemingly%20still%20does%20not%20know%20why%20Altman%20was%20fired%2C%20telling%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-20%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-signals-willingness-to-have-altman-rejoin-openai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBloomberg%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BThe%20board%20has%20not%20talked%20about%20anything%20that%20Sam%20did%20other%20than%20some%20breakdown%20in%20communications.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommentators%20had%20speculated%20that%20Microsoft%20would%20be%20after%20an%20OpenAI%20board%20seat%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20a%20more%20formalized%20communication%20system%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20up%20with%20the%20suspicious%20letter%20from%20'former%20employees'%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENever%20one%20to%20be%20left%20out%20of%20the%20drama%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20also%20weighed%20into%20the%20chaos%20on%20Tuesday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1727096607752282485%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20sharing%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20supposedly%20from%20former%20OpenAI%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20has%20yet%20to%20verify%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20letter.%20It%20was%20notably%20unsigned%2C%20and%20the%20original%20source%20had%20been%20removed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20made%20unverified%20claims%20about%20Alman%20and%20Brockman%20over%20their%20management%20at%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThroughout%20our%20time%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20we%20witnessed%20a%20disturbing%20pattern%20of%20deceit%20and%20manipulation%20by%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20driven%20by%20their%20insatiable%20pursuit%20of%20achieving%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20(AGI).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20OpenAI%20employees%20have%20dismissed%20the%20claims%20on%20X%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20attacks%20on%20Greg's%20and%20Sam's%20character%20say%20more%20about%20the%20accusers.%20Totally%20false%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Welinder%2C%20a%20VP%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnpew%2Fstatus%2F1727111730571211261%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%2C%20said%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20we%20argue%20about%20GPU%20allocation%20all%20the%20time!%20Sam's%20job%20is%20to%20decide.%20Ofc%20someone%20will%20be%20disappointed.%20Grow%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ousting-sam-altman-big-questions-microsoft-fired-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700740920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655cd1674ca513d8242cd0af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ousting-sam-altman-big-questions-microsoft-fired-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20one%20of%20the%20most%20confusing%20weeks%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20history%2C%20here's%20what%20we%20still%20don't%20know%20about%20Sam%20Altman's%20firing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ousting-sam-altman-big-questions-microsoft-fired-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20American%20spending%20Thanksgiving%20as%20a%20combat%20nurse%20under%20fire%20on%20the%20frontline%20in%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221559%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rebekah%20Maciorowski.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655644e64ca513d8242a9c4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221169%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERebekah%20Maciorowski%20in%20front