%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Joy%20Buolamwini%20Algorithmic%20Justice%20League%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65173f15846a2f0019a11e3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Joy%20Buolamwini%2C%20Algorithmic%20Justice%20League%3Cp%3EPoet%20of%20Code%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Buolamwini's%20research%20found%20that%20major%20tech%20companies'%20AI-driven%20facial%20recognition%20tools%20were%20deeply%20biased%20and%20inaccurate.%20In%202016%2C%20she%20founded%20the%20Algorithmic%20Justice%20League%20after%20her%20MIT%20master's%20thesis%20showed%20how%20the%20data%20sets%20used%20to%20train%20several%20facial%20recognition%20tools%20were%20%26quot%3Boverwhelmingly%26quot%3B%20trained%20on%20images%20of%20lighter-skinned%20people%20and%20had%20huge%20gaps%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20recognize%20women%20of%20color%20accurately.%20Recently%2C%20she%20coined%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20coded%20gaze%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20idea%20that%20society%20will%20be%20looked%20upon%20by%20tools%20trained%20on%20data%20from%20the%20past%20that%20does%20little%20but%20promulgate%20existing%20biases.%20Buolamwini%20is%20now%20the%20%26quot%3Bartist%20in%20chief%26quot%3B%20and%20president%20of%20the%20AJL%20and%20recently%20wrote%20a%20book%20%26quot%3BUnmasking%20AI%3A%20My%20Mission%20to%20Protect%20What%20is%20Human%20in%20a%20World%20of%20Machines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EElham%20Tabassi%2C%20NIST%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elham%20Tabassi%20NIST%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6555346336d588dc55d12c10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22288%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElham%20Tabassi%2C%20NIST%3Cp%3ENIST%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETabassi%20wrote%20the%20first-ever%20AI%20Risk%20Management%20Framework%20for%20the%20US%20National%20Institute%20of%20Standards%20and%20Technology.%20The%20well-received%20framework%20explored%20the%20good%20and%20bad%20of%20AI%20and%20everything%20in%20between%2C%20and%20it%20offered%20practical%20guidelines%20on%20avoiding%20its%20risks.%20Its%20success%20led%20the%20White%20House%20to%20direct%20NIST%20to%20form%20a%20new%20AI%20working%20group.%20Tabassi%20has%20worked%20at%20the%20NIST%20for%20nearly%2025%20years%20and%20last%20year%20became%20its%20first%20Associate%20Director%20for%20Emerging%20Technologies%20at%20its%20Information%20Technology%20Lab.%20Some%20of%20her%20earlier%20work%20for%20NIST%20focused%20on%20machine%20learning%20projects%20around%20biometric%20data.%20Tabassi%20also%20holds%20several%20leadership%20roles%2C%20including%20vice-chair%20of%20the%20Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development's%20working%20party%20on%20AI%20Governance.%20She%20was%20educated%20at%20Iran's%20Sharif%20University%20of%20Technology%20and%20then%20Santa%20Clara%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EChris%20Wiggins%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22790%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chris%20Wiggins%20The%20New%20York%20Times%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65174f93846a2f0019a12197%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChris%20Wiggins%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20is%20the%20news%20industry's%20leading%20subscription%20success%20story%2C%20with%20nearly%2010%20million%20readers%20paying%20for%20print%20or%20digital%20access%20and%20subscription%20revenue%20that's%20surpassed%20advertising.%20Much%20credit%20goes%20to%20its%20chief%20data%20scientist%20Wiggins%2C%20whose%20team%20uses%20machine%20learning%20to%20figure%20out%20which%20readers%20will%20subscribe%20and%20who%20will%20cancel.%20This%20work%20was%20previously%20done%20by%20surveys.%20Wiggins%20also%20helped%20create%20software%20that%20predicted%20how%20readers%20would%20feel%20after%20reading%20an%20article%2C%20which%20is%20used%20for%20what%20the%20Times%20calls%20%26quot%3Bperspective%20targeting%26quot%3B%20of%20ads.%20Wiggins%2C%20who%20became%20the%20Times'%20first%20person%20in%20the%20position%20in%202014%2C%20has%20several%20other%20roles%2C%20including%20associate%20professor%20of%20applied%20mathematics%20at%20Columbia%20and%20co-founder%20of%20the%20nonprofit%20HackNY.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECamille%20Carlton%2C%20Center%20for%20Humane%20Technology%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Camille%20Carlton%20Center%20for%20Human%20Technology%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65173dc0846a2f0019a11df7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECamille%20Carlton%2C%20Center%20for%20Human%20Technology%3Cp%3ECenter%20for%20Human%20Technology%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarlton%20describes%20her%20path%20to%20working%20on%20AI%20policy%20as%20%26quot%3Bnonlinear.%26quot%3B%20She%20studied%20international%20affairs%20and%20had%20a%20longstanding%20interest%20in%20how%20society%20could%20%26quot%3Brealign%20capital%20with%20the%20things%20we%20really%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20something%20she%20links%20to%20her%20upbringing%20by%20parents%20who%20fled%20Cuba%20as%20refugees.%20After%20seeing%20how%20divided%20her%20family%20became%20around%20the%202016%20election%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20information%20they%20saw%20on%20sites%20like%20Facebook%2C%20Carlton%20was%20inspired%20to%20study%20technology%20and%20society.%20She%20now%20works%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Humane%20Technology%2C%20advising%20policymakers%20on%20laws%20and%20regulations%20for%20AI.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20most%20scared%20about%20how%20these%20systems%20will%20further%20entrench%20deep%20power%20asymmetries%20and%20socioeconomic%20inequality%2C%26quot%3B%20Carlton%20said.%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20a%20few%20large%20companies%20run%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20shaping%20everything.%20We%20want%20something%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDavid%20Evan%20Harris%2C%20UC%20Berkeley%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20Evan%20Harris%20UC%20Berkeley%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65173ca0846a2f0019a11d95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDavid%20Evan%20Harris%2C%20UC%20Berkeley%3Cp%3EUC%20Berkeley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20taught%20courses%20on%20technology%20and%20AI%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%20and%20researched%20the%20intersection%20of%20democracy%20and%20AI%20for%20years.%20He%20recently%20worked%20on%20Meta's%20Responsible%20AI%20team%20but%20is%20now%20ringing%20the%20alarm%20on%20risks%20posed%20by%20open-source%20AI%20models.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20great%20to%20influence%20that%20company%20from%20the%20inside%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%20Harris%20previously%20worked%20with%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Future%20to%20forecast%20AI's%20long-term%20impact%20on%20society%2C%20and%20he%20recently%20advised%20the%20White%20House%20and%20the%20European%20Commission%20on%20considerations%20for%20AI%20regulation.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20Chancellor's%20Public%20Scholar%20at%20Berkeley%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20for%20the%20Psychology%20of%20Technology%20Institute%2C%20an%20Affiliate%20Scholar%20at%20the%20CITRIS%20Policy%20Lab%20on%20the%20regulation%20of%20AI%20and%20social%20media%2C%20and%20a%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20International%20Computer%20Science%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAlexandru%20Costin%2C%20Adobe%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexandru%20Costin%20Adobe%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65175426846a2f0019a121fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexandru%20Costi%2C%20Adobe%3Cp%3EAdobe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECostin%20is%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20generative%20AI%20and%20Sensei%20at%20content%20editing%20giant%20Adobe.%20He%20led%20the%20development%20of%20Adobe%20Firefly%2C%20its%20new%20suite%20of%20creative%20generative%20AI%20models.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20creators%20feared%20AI%20models%20would%20steal%20their%20work%2C%20Adobe%20stood%20out%20by%20promising%20Firefly%20would%20only%20be%20trained%20on%20content%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20or%20that%20Adobe%20had%20rights%20to%20through%20its%20popular%20stock%20image%20service%2C%20Adobe%20Stock.%20Adobe%20followed%20that%20by%20announcing%20it%20would%20pay%20bonuses%20to%20Stock%20contributors%20whose%20content%20is%20being%20used%20to%20train%20Firefly.%20The%20native%20Romanian%20was%20an%20entrepreneur%20who%20sold%20his%20web%20tools%20company%20InterAKT%20to%20Adobe.%20He%20ran%20Adobe%20Romania%20for%2010%20years%20before%20relocating%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAviv%20Ovadya%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aviv%20Ovadya%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65174e3b5640b20019d78834%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearcher%20Aviv%20Ovadya%3Cp%3EAviv%20Ovadya%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOvadya%20was%20early%20to%20ring%20the%20bell%20on%20the%20potential%20dangers%20of%20AI.%202016%20saw%20the%20start%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Binfocalypse%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20what%20was%20then%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bsynthetic%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20later%20called%20deep%20fakes%20and%20now%20generative%20AI.%20He%20has%20researched%20AI%20advancements%2C%20misinformation%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20social%20media%20on%20society%20and%20democracy.%20He's%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Social%20Media%20Responsibility%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%