e%20of%20Mars%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20object%20of%20that%20size%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20impact%20into%20the%20planet%20rather%20than%20just%20to%20be%20captured%20in%20orbit%2C%26quot%3B%20Sara%20Russell%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20planetary%20sciences%20at%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELunar%20samples%20brought%20back%20during%20the%20Apollo%20missions%20put%20a%20final%20nail%20in%20that%20hypothesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20analyzed%20the%20isotope%20makeup%20of%20these%20samples.%20Isotopes%20are%20forms%20of%20atoms%20that%20have%20the%20same%20chemical%20function%2C%20but%20carry%20a%20different%20number%20of%20neutrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20use%20isotopes%20as%20a%20fingerprint%2C%20which%20are%20very%20distinctive%2C%26quot%3B%20Russell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20space%20rocks%20form%20independently%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20tell%20them%20apart%20with%20isotopes.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frelativity-space-3d-printed-rocket-mars-musk-spacex-bezos-launch-2023-3%3F_gl%3D1*13p0krb*_ga*MTc3NTE4NzkyNC4xNjg0MTQxMjIx*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMDczNDkzNC40NjEuMS4xNzAwNzM0OTM0LjYwLjAuMA..%26r%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMars%3C%2Fa%3E%20rock%20looks%20different%20from%20an%20Earth%20rock%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20moon%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20is%20made%20up%20of%20the%20same%20isotopes%20as%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20they%20must%20be%20genetically%20linked%20somehow%20because%20every%20other%20body%20in%20the%20solar%20system%20has%20got%20a%20different%20isotope%20signature%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22985%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pictures%20taken%20by%20a%20satellite%20show%20the%20moon%20crossing%20the%20Earth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647f4083a52c4b001936bd7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22554%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20animation%20of%20the%20moon%20rotating%20around%20the%20Earth.%20Scientists%20are%20starting%20to%20uncover%20the%20moon's%20tiny%20but%20mighty%20effect%20on%20Earth's%20earthquakes.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FNOAA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20moon%20formed%20alongside%20the%20Earth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accretion%20hypothesis%20ties%20the%20moon%20to%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20Earth.%20This%20theory%20suggests%20both%20objects%20emerged%20from%20the%20same%20cosmic%20cloud%20of%20dust%20around%204.6%20billion%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Earth%2C%20per%20that%20theory%2C%20would%20have%20been%20the%20greedier%20twin%2C%20pulling%20more%20material%20to%20its%20side%20during%20its%20early%20accretion%2C%20which%20led%20to%20its%20bigger%20size%2C%20molten%20core%2C%20and%20stronger%20gravity.%20The%20moon%2C%20then%2C%20would%20have%20been%20pulled%20into%20Earth's%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20while%20the%20moon%20and%20the%20Earth%20share%20isotopes%2C%20the%20way%20they%20put%20them%20together%20is%20very%20different.%20The%20moon%20is%20made%20up%20of%20much%20less%20sodium%20and%20iron%20than%20the%20Earth%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20expect%20that%20if%20it%20formed%20from%20the%20same%20cloud%2C%20the%20same%20mixture%20of%20material%2C%20it%20would%20end%20up%20with%20roughly%20the%20same%20composition%2C%20it%20might%20just%20be%20smaller%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Russel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20actually%2C%20it's%20completely%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20moon%20was%20a%20glob%20of%20material%20shed%20by%20the%20Earth%20as%20it%20started%20spinning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20theory%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20our%20constant%20companion%20is%20not%20very%20flattering.%20This%20one%20argues%20that%20the%20moon%20is%20just%20a%20bit%20of%20excess%20baby%20fat%20our%20Earth%20shed%20early%20on%20in%20its%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20picture%20shows%20the%20moon%20showing%20against%20the%20daylight%20sky%20behind%20a%20mountain%20ridge.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647f4479a52c4b001936be81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22693%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20moon%20also%20pulls%20as%20the%20earth%2C%20scientists%20have%20found.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20fission%20theory%2C%20as%20the%20Earth%20started%20spinning%20faster%2C%20part%20of%20its%20material%20spun%20off%2C%20and%20then%20miraculously%20stopped%20exactly%20where%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20to%20create%20a%20body%20in%20Earth's%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20physics%20is%20not%20on%20the%20side%20of%20this%20theory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20difficult%20to%20shed%20such%20a%20big%20mass%20of%20rock%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20quickly%20the%20planet%20was%20spinning%20at%20the%20time%2C%20said%20Russell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20might%20happen%20for%20an%20asteroid%2C%20but%20not%20something%20as%20big%20as%20the%20planet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20with%20that%20theory%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoon-missions-why-astronauts-have-not-returned-2018-7%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20moon%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20have%20been%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20fly%20off%20toward%20the%20sun%20or%20fall%20back%20to%20Earth%20than%20to%20stay%20in%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Mars-sized%20planet%20crashed%20into%20the%20early%20Earth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20us%20with%20one%20last%20hypothesis%2C%20the%20giant%20impact%20theory.%20While%20this%20hypothesis%20has%20the%20most%20scientific%20support%2C%20it%20is%20arguably%20the%20one%20that%20requires%20the%20biggest%20leap%20of%20the%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20theory%20suggests%20that%20around%204.5%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20Mars-sized%20planet%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falien-planet-inside-earth-explain-where-moon-comes-from-theia-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETheia%3C%2Fa%3E%20crossed%20paths%20with%20a%20new%20Earth%20that%20had%20just%20started%20accreting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20collision%20between%20the%20two%20planets%20created%20a%20humongous%20explosion%2C%20100%20million%20times%20bigger%20than%20the%20impact%20that%20wiped%20out%20the%20dinosaurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20animation%20shows%20Theia%20crashing%20into%20the%20moon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65424f18b788914e554d33ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20animation%20shows%20Theia%20crashing%20into%20the%20moon.%3Cp%3EVincent%20Eke%20and%20Jacob%20A.%20Kegerreis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20this%20theory%2C%20the%20blow%20was%20so%20brutal%20that%20Theia%20kicked%20some%20of%20the%20Earth's%20material%20into%20space%2C%20which%20eventually%20turned%20into%20the%20moon.%20Theia%20disappeared%20by%20melting%20into%20the%20mess%20of%20molten%20rock%20that%20would%20eventually%20become%20the%20Earth%20and%20the%20moon%20as%20we%20know%20them%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subtle%20difference%20between%20the%20Earth%20and%20the%20moon%2C%20then%2C%20would%20be%20explained%20by%20Theia%20grazing%20the%20Earth's%20mantle%20but%20avoiding%20its%20iron%20core%2C%20which%20could%20explain%20why%20the%20moon%20is%20so%20iron-poor%2C%20per%20Russell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20process%20may%20have%20taken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fsolar-system%2Fcollision-may-have-formed-the-moon-in-mere-hours-simulations-reveal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20a%20few%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20sounds%20far-fetched%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20Apollo%20samples%2C%20it%20has%20quickly%20become%20the%20leading%20theory%20for%20how%20the%20moon%20formed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20one%20of%20the%20absolute%20triumphs%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapollo-11-facts-about-nasa-moon-landing-2019-7%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Apollo%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Russell.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20Apollo%2C%20people%20honestly%20had%20no%20clue%20which%20of%20these%20models%20was%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20moon%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApollo%20showed%20clearly%20that%20the%20moon%20has%20such%20great%20similarities%20to%20each%20other%2C%20that%20they%20must%20be%20somehow%20linked%20in%20some%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20giant-impact%20theory%20is%20not%20without%20its%20issues.%20We%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20Theia%20came%20from%20and%20the%20planet%20left%20no%20evidence%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20that%20it's%20not%20quite%20clear%20why%20the%20moon%20and%20the%20Earth%20would%20be%20so%20similar%20if%20they%20picked%20up%20bits%20of%20Theia%20along%20the%20way.%20Models%20suggest%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20the%20moon%20should%20be%20made%20up%20of%20Theia%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F19275-moon-formation.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Space.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possibility%20is%20that%20at%20the%20point%20of%20impact%2C%20Theia%20mixed%20in%20so%20thoroughly%20with%20both%20the%20Earth%20and%20the%20moon%20that%20these%20are%20virtually%20indistinguishable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20possibility%20is%20that%20Theia%20was%20almost%20a%20twin%20of%20the%20Earth%2C%20created%20in%20the%20same%20corner%20of%20the%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20working%20to%20reconcile%20these%20finer%20points%20of%20the%20giant-impact%20theory.%20Modeling%20can%20explore%20the%20angle%20at%20which%20the%20planet%20hit%20the%20Earth%20and%20how%20its%20material%20mixed%20in%20with%20the%20Earth's%20mantle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20study%20suggested%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falien-planet-inside-earth-explain-where-moon-comes-from-theia-2023-11%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinent-sized%20chunks%20of%20an%20alien%20world%20may%20be%20hiding%20deep%20within%20our%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20explain%20the%20weird%20structures%20that%20appear%20to%20be%20surrounding%20Earth's%20core.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHongping%20Deng%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20computational%20physics%20from%20the%20Chinese%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%2C%20ran%20computer%20simulations%20tracking%20100%20million%20virtual%20particles%20from%20the%20moment%20Theia%20may%20have%20crashed%20into%20the%20Earth%20through%20to%20millions%20of%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20these%20simulations%2C%20the%20scientists%20were%20able%20to%20show%20that%20some%20fragments%20of%20Theia%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%202%25%20of%20the%20whole%20mass%20of%20the%20Earth%20%E2%80%94could%20have%20survived%20inside%20our%20planet%2C%20slowly%20sinking%20through%20the%20mantle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20artist's%20impression%20shows%20an%20astronaut%20sitting%20back%20while%20taking%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20Earth%20rising%20behind%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%20with%20a%20smartphone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c52231048ff200190d8dd2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20future%20of%20moon%20exploration%20might%20look%20like%20if%20phone%20networks%20are%20brought%20there.%3Cp%3Epeepo%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%