20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20acknowledged%20the%20uneven%20cumulative%20historical%20responsibilities%20in%20causing%20global%20warming%2C%20and%20the%20disproportionately%20higher%20risk%20faced%20by%20countries%20least%20responsible%20for%20the%20climatic%20changes%2C%20and%20called%20for%20scaling%20up%20of%20international%20financial%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CLow-%20and%20lower-middle-income%20countries%20are%20in%20the%20greatest%20need%20of%20affordable%20finance%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%20India%2C%20which%20is%20listed%20India%20among%20lower-middle-income%20countries%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfaces%20the%20challenge%20of%20mobilising%20investment%20to%20achieve%20its%20ambitious%20clean%20energy%20transition%20plans%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20the%20global%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20be%20reduced%E2%80%9D%20by%2028-42%25%2C%20compared%20to%20where%20they%20are%20headed%20under%20policies%20currently%20in%20place%2C%20to%20be%20able%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%20well%20below%202.0%C2%B0C%20and%201.5%C2%B0C%2C%20respectively%2C%20from%20pre-industrial%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20failure%20to%20stringently%20reduce%20emissions%20in%20high-income%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20which%20bear%20the%20greatest%20responsibility%20for%20past%20emissions%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20limit%20emissions%20growth%20in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20which%20account%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20current%20emissions%2C%20unprecedented%20action%20is%20now%20needed%20by%20all%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20suggested%20that%20the%20situation%20warranted%20high-income%20countries%20to%20further%20accelerate%20domestic%20emissions%20reductions%2C%20committing%20to%20reaching%20net%20zero%20emissions%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%20providing%20financial%20and%20technical%20support%20to%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CCountries%20with%20greater%20capacity%20and%20responsibility%20for%20emissions%20will%20need%20to%20take%20more%20ambitious%20action%20and%20provide%20financial%20and%20technical%20support%20to%20developing%20nations%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20the%20situation%20requires%20that%20pressing%20development%20needs%20must%20be%20met%20alongside%20a%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20the%20report%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20low%20and%20lower-middle-income%20countries%20are%20already%20saddled%20with%20debt%20and%20receive%20disproportionately%20low%20clean%20energy%20investments.%20Besides%2C%20they%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20volatile%20fossil%20fuel%20markets%20either%20as%20exporters%20or%20importers%20and%20may%20face%20future%20stranded%20fossil%20fuel%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CInternational%20financial%20assistance%20will%20have%20to%20be%20significantly%20scaled%20up%2C%20with%20new%20public%20and%20private%20sources%20of%20capital%20restructured%20through%20financing%20mechanisms%20that%20lower%20costs%20of%20capital.%20These%20include%20debt%20financing%2C%20long-term%20concessional%20finance%2C%20guarantees%2C%20and%20catalytic%20finance%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20EGR%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20suggested%20that%20the%20coming%20edition%20of%20the%20global%20climate%20summit%2C%20known%20as%20COP28%2C%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Dubai%20from%20November%2030%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20ensure%20that%20international%20support%20is%20provided%20for%20the%20development%20of%20such%20ambitious%20roadmaps.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20EGR%20also%20acknowledged%20the%20massive%20challenges%20that%20India%20faces%20in%20the%20low-carbon%20transition%20due%20to%20the%20deep%20coal%20economy.%20Major%20coal%20producers%20like%20China%2C%20India%2C%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20%E2%80%9Cface%20the%20risk%20of%20stranded%20assets%2C%20large-scale%20unemployment%20and%20energy%20insecurity%20if%20coal%20is%20rapidly%20phased%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGlobal%20climate%20financing%20mainly%20involves%20funding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fintroduction-to-mitigation%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fintroduction-to-mitigation%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw13_y6Kg4DxJEMgn-Ekq4fB%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emitigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20(transition%20to%20the%20low-emission%20economy)%20initiatives%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fadaptation-and-resilience%2Fthe-big-picture%2Fintroduction%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fadaptation-and-resilience%2Fthe-big-picture%2Fintroduction%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0X8BnhLoquIMsqwt9oJbmM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadaptation%20and%20resilience%3C%2Fa%3E-building%20measures%2C%20and%20covering%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fadaptation-and-resilience%2Fthe-big-picture%2Fintroduction%23loss-and-damage%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fadaptation-and-resilience%2Fthe-big-picture%2Fintroduction%2523loss-and-damage%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2WtSilVGQ_zkMmaT9cYG1s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloss%20and%20damages%3C%2Fa%3E%20suffered%20by%20poorer%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Article%209%20of%20the%202015%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ffiles%2Fmeetings%2Fparis_nov_2015%2Fapplication%2Fpdf%2Fcop_auv_template_4b_new__1.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ffiles%2Fmeetings%2Fparis_nov_2015%2Fapplication%2Fpdf%2Fcop_auv_template_4b_new__1.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1SC1mbsUFayruApNkRqn4h%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParis%20Agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20developed%20country%20parties%20are%20to%20provide%20financial%20resources%20to%20assist%20developing%20country%20parties%20with%20respect%20to%20both%20mitigation%20and%20adaptation%20in%20continuation%20of%20their%20existing%20obligations%20under%20the%20Convention.%20The%20aspect%20of%20loss%20and%20damage%20was%20recognised%20during%20the%202022%20edition%20of%20the%20climate%20summit%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20COP27.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFunding%20on%20all%20these%20aspects%20is%20scheduled%20to%20be%20discussed%20during%20COP28.%20India%20environment%20minister%20Bhupendra%20Yadav%20had%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20lack%20of%20accessible%20climate%20finance%20during%20COP%2027%20and%20said%20that%20the%20commitment%20made%20by%20the%20developed%20countries%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20a%20meager%20amount%20and%20remains%20unachieved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndia%20is%20expected%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20of%20funding%20during%20COP%2028%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Furgent-need-for-higher-climate-action-to-limit-global-warming-unep-report%5C%22%3EUrgent%20Need%20for%20Higher%20Climate%20Action%20to%20Limit%20Global%20Warming%3A%20UNEP%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20funding%20challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndia%20has%20a%20unique%20space%20in%20this%20whole%20discussion%20about%20cutting%20emissions%20and%20access%20to%20necessary%20funding.%20It%20is%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20emitters%E2%80%9D%20currently%20but%20has%20a%20significantly%20low%20historical%20responsibility%20compared%20to%20its%20population%20and%20its%20per%20capita%20emission%20stands%20less%20than%20half%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmong%20the%20G20%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20which%20as%20a%20group%20accounts%20for%20three-quarters%20of%20current%20global%20emissions%20%E2%80%93%20India%20has%20the%20lowest%20per%20capita%20emission%2C%20but%20is%20also%20projected%20to%20record%20the%20highest%20increase%20in%20per%20capita%20emission%20till%202030.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20India%20faces%20a%20high%20level%20of%20vulnerability%20to%20erratic%20climatic%20patterns%2C%20including%20floods%2C%20droughts%2C%20other%20natural%20disasters%2C%20and%20crop%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAll%20these%20aspects%20make%20India%E2%80%99s%20requirement%20for%20international%20financial%20assistance%20towards%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20all%20the%20more%20just%2C%20experts%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Harjeet%20Singh%2C%20head%20of%20global%20political%20strategy%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimatenetwork.org%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fclimatenetwork.org%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0CtH0XG3XuuVPziK0Gr1t1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimate%20Action%20Network%20International%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20global%20network%20of%20more%20than%201%2C900%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20the%20EGR%20certainly%20strengthens%20India%E2%80%99s%20case%20for%20greater%20access%20to%20international%20funding%20for%20necessary%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20EGR%20shows%20again%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20climate%20action%20funding%20requirement%20is%20disproportionately%20higher%20than%20its%20contribution%20to%20global%20warming.%20Data%20from%20past%20reports%20showed%20that%20about%2085%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20green%20finance%20has%20been%20domestic.%20Despite%20showing%20a%20significant%20interest%20in%20taking%20climate-friendly%20measures%2C%20India%20has%20mostly%20been%20on%20its%20own%20in%20meeting%20its%20commitments%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20vast%20contrast%20between%20the%20current%20trajectory%20and%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20goals%20%E2%80%93%20as%20revealed%20in%20the%20EGR%20%E2%80%93%20highlights%20the%20failure%20of%20rich%20countries%20to%20meet%20their%20climate%20commitments%2C%20he%20argued.%20Developed%20countries%20%E2%80%9Chave%20not%20only%20fallen%20short%20in%20reducing%20emissions%20but%20also%20in%20providing%20essential%20financial%20support%20to%20nations%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20impacts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Dhruba%20Purkayastha%2C%20India-director%20of%20the%20US-headquartered%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climatepolicyinitiative.org%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.climatepolicyinitiative.org%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0aEtK9_0NzPffFXKIhbykG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimate%20Policy%20Initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20analysis%20and%20advisory%20organisation%20with%20expertise%20in%20finance%20and%20policy%2C%20the%20EGR%20reiterates%20what%20has%20been%20said%20time%20and%20again%20that%20the%20world%20is%20not%20on%20track%20for%201.5%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20same%20holds%20true%20for%20both%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries%20but%20the%20problem%20is%20bigger%20for%20developing%20countries%20including%20India.%20Developing%20countries%20need%20much%20more%20global%20concessional%20finance%20than%20what%20is%20contributed%20to%20at%20present%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20with%20the%20increasing%20frequency%20and%20severity%20of%20climate-related%20events%20and%20disasters%20in%20India%2C%20adaptation%20is%20its%20greater%20priority.%20There%20are%20other%20sustainable%20development%20goals%2C%20such%20as%20poverty%20and%20hunger%20reduction%2C%20education%2C%20social%20and%20environmental%20protection%20and%20healthcare%2C%20which%20are%20not%20always%20aligned%20with%20climate%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Purkayastha%2C%20given%20India%E2%80%99s%20critical%20importance%20for%20the%20world%20to%20meet%20its%20climate%20goals%2C%20it%20is%20important%20for%20the%20world%20to%20get%20a%20low%20carbon%20transition%20in%20India%20right%2C%20as%20India%20would%20continue%20to%20grow%20and%20so%20would%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CUnless%20there%20is%20a%20mechanism%20to%20pay%20for%20incremental%20carbon%20emissions%20mitigated%2C%20and%20paid%20for%20through%20some%20institutional%20form%20of%20bilateral%20%E2%80%98sovereign%20to%20sovereign%E2%80%99%20funding%20as%20provided%20under%20Article%206.2%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20absolute%20carbon%20emissions%20would%20see%20any%20reduction%20in%20the%20near%20future%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESingh%20also%20thinks%20that%20though%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FTC5_4_Cochairs%2520draft%2520text_Rev1.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FTC5_4_Cochairs%252520draft%252520text_Rev1.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0VYO8Dl2wryGRXoCHqAIUl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20released%20draft%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20loss%20and%20damage%20funding%20arrangement%20makes%20India%20eligible%20to%20be%20a%20recipient%2C%20India%20should%20not%20be%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20receiving%20money%20from%20this%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CSmaller%20and%20poorer%20countries%2C%20contributing%20minimally%20to%20global%20warming%20and%20with%20limited%20resources%20to%20combat%20severe%20impacts%2C%20need%20the%20loss%20and%20damage%20finance%20more%20than%20India%20does%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAarti%20Khosla%2C%20director%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimatetrends.in%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fclimatetrends.in%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw193xtTSGO9F1GAj_SJwmwt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimate%20Trends%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20research%2C%20consultancy%2C%20and%20capacity-building%20initiative%2C%20agreed.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CIn%20comparison%20to%20many%20other%20least%20developed%20countries%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20range%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20the%20first%20qualifier%20for%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20main%20requirement%20is%20public%20investments%20in%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20needs%20public%20funds%20big%20time.%20It%20could%20be%20multilateral%20banks%20investing%20in%20clean%20projects%2C%20or%20other%20instruments%20like%20sovereign%20wealth%20funds.%20Technology%20will%20be%20there%20if%20finance%20is%20available%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khosla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16114924%2FUntitled-design-8.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16114924%2FUntitled-design-8.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16114924%2FUntitled-design-8-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16114924%2FUntitled-design-8-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-636374%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECOP28%20president%20Sultan%20al%20Jaber.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40AtlanticCouncil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeadership%20role%20at%20COP28%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPurkayastha%20also%20thinks%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20COP%2028%20should%20not%20be%20limited%20to%20seeking%20funds%20for%20itself%20alone%20but%20play%20a%20leadership%20role%20for%20the%20Global%20South%20%E2%80%93%20the%20developing%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20which%20require%20access%20to%20concessional%20funds%20for%20the%20clean%20energy%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20negotiating%20concessional%20financing%20for%20the%20global%20south%20is%20important%2C%E2%80%9D%20Purkayastha%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20a%20global%20institutional%20system%20to%20socialise%20the%20cost%20of%20capital%2C%20availability%20of%20data%20and%20information%2C%20and%20transfer%20of%20climate%20technology%20for%20emissions%20reduction%20as%20a%20global%20public%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20this%20process%2C%20India%20(the%20outgoing%20G20%20presidency)%20and%20other%20large%20developing%20countries%20like%20Brazil%20(incoming%20G20%20presidency)%20could%20play%20an%20anchor%20role%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20should%20be%20a%20settlement%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FWorkshopArticle6_Infra.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FWorkshopArticle6_Infra.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700808638168000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2eSd7pxj8F6Wx0Gay38MOk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArticle%206.2%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20and%20it%20should%20be%20finalised%20who%20pays%20for%20the%20emission%20reduction%20that%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20or%20South%20Africa%20does.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20said%20that%20leaving%20the%20financing%20aspect%20on%20the%20carbon%20market%20is%20not%20working%20and%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20carbon%20markets%20would%20play%20any%20significant%20role%2C%20except%20for%20a%20few%20specific%20countries%2Fprojects.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20through%20bilateral%20systems%20and%20India%20could%20push%20for%20the%20same%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Purkayastha.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700735723000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewi