%2C%20she%20thinks%20that%20role%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Beven%20more%20stressful%26quot%3B%20than%20top%20leadership.%20She%20said%20it%20also%20seems%20to%20age%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevika%2C%20whose%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%20but%20asked%20to%20use%20a%20pseudonym%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions%2C%20knows%20holding%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-manager-before-i-was-prepared-what-wish-i-knew-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagerial%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20something%20she's%20really%20interested%20in.%20That's%20partly%20because%20it%20seems%20like%20a%20high-pressure%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevika%20said%20younger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-and-gen-z-dont-want-to-be-managers-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20like%20her%20may%20not%20see%20moving%20to%20a%20manager%20role%20as%20worth%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20%26quot%3Bit's%20just%20giving%20up%20too%20much%20of%20your%20personal%20life%20and%20then%20life%20is%20short.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bmight%20as%20well%20individually%20contribute%26quot%3B%20while%20making%20%26quot%3BX%20amount%20of%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevika%20isn't%20alone.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visier.com%2Fblog%2Fnew-research-individual-contributors-shun-management%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EVisier%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20from%20August%20of%201%2C000%20US-based%20full-time%20workers%20found%20just%2038%25%20of%20%26quot%3Bindividual%20contributors%20are%20interested%20in%20becoming%20a%20people%20manager%20at%20their%20current%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20blog%20post%20about%20the%20results%20stated.%20Andrea%20Derler%2C%20principal%20of%20research%20and%20customer%20value%20at%20Visier%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20there%20could%20be%20a%20succession%20gap%20at%20companies%20if%20they%20aren't%20investing%20in%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanagers-burned-out-looking-for-new-jobs-more-than-subordinates-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupporting%20their%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDerler%20said%20the%20survey%20takers%20%26quot%3Bare%20worried%20about%20increased%20stress%20and%20pressures.%26quot%3B%20That%20includes%20feeling%20extra%20pressure%20from%20senior%20management%2C%20Derler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20results%20also%20suggest%20that%20some%20participants%20believe%20moving%20into%20management%20will%20mean%20working%20longer%20or%20more%20hours%2C%20and%20some%20are%20happy%20with%20their%20current%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20are%20still%20ways%20to%20be%20a%20leader%20in%20the%20workplace%20without%20managing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Vallely%20is%20another%20millennial%20who%20is%20happy%20in%20his%20individual%20contributor%20role%20and%20not%20particularly%20inclined%20to%20move%20into%20management.%20He's%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20tech%20company%20Ibotta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVallely%20said%20he%20used%20to%20think%20that%20advancing%20his%20career%20meant%20working%20in%20management%20but%20found%20there%20can%20be%20other%20opportunities%20for%20leadership.%20For%20example%2C%20engineers%20at%20his%20company%20can%20mentor%20employees%20without%20taking%20a%20managerial%20role%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20this%20to%20be%20true%20for%20engineers%20in%20general.%20He%20said%20people%20can%20still%20do%20leadership%20work%20on%20an%20individual%20contributor%20career%20path%20and%20that%20this%20can%20be%20a%20way%20organizations%20don't%20lose%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20and%20brightest%20and%20most%20experienced%20engineers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20hurdles%20Vallely%20sees%20in%20being%20a%20manager%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20solving%20people's%20problems%2C%20which%20don't%20stop%20because%20the%20workday%20ended%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%2C%20to%20me%2C%20seems%20something%20that%20would%20be%20harder%20to%20separate%20from%20after%20the%20workday%20is%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20current%20role%2C%20he%20has%20time%20to%20step%20away%20from%20his%20tasks%20to%20gain%20a%20fresh%20perspective%20but%20isn't%20sure%20he'd%20have%20the%20same%20luxury%20if%20he%20was%20a%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECompanies%20can%20address%20the%20succession%20gap%20now%20before%20it's%20too%20late%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20employers%20worried%20about%20the%20pipeline%20of%20potential%20managers%2C%20Derler%20recommends%20helping%20assist%20workers%20coming%20into%20management%20with%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bmanager%20onboarding%20support.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnboarding%20someone%20means%20to%20help%20them%20acclimatize%20in%20the%20new%20company%2C%20and%20the%20new%20team%2C%20building%20relationships%2C%20understanding%20expectations%2C%20learning%20opportunities%20and%20so%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Derler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20new%20managers%20don't%20often%20get%20that%20learning%20opportunity%20and%20then%20form%20bad%20habits%20that%20are%20hard%20to%20eradicate%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20organizations%20can%20do%20is%20think%20about%20who%20they%20are%20considering%20for%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDerler%20said%20organizations%20typically%20look%20for%20workers%20with%20high%20performance%2C%20but%20these%20people%20aren't%20always%20best%20suited%20for%20management.%20Instead%2C%20employers%20should%20focus%20on%20qualities%20like%20an%20enterprise%20mindset%20or%20situations%20where%20an%20employee%20collaborated%20with%20others%20or%20supported%20coworkers%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Visier%20survey%20found%2071%25%20of%20respondents%2C%20including%20those%20who%20don't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20be%20people%20managers%2C%20said%20better%20compensation%20would%20be%20a%20top%20incentive%20for%20becoming%20this%20kind%20of%20manager.%20Derler%20was%20surprised%20by%20this%20result%20because%20research%20shows%20people%20traditionally%20wanted%20to%20take%20on%20manager%20roles%20so%20they%20could%20help%20more%20with%20company%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20pay%20increase%20would%20be%20nice%2C%20Vallely%20said%2C%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Bit's%20more%20important%20to%20do%20what%20you%20love.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20turned%20down%20a%20promotion%3F%20What%20are%20your%20thoughts%20on%20promotions%20and%20moving%20up%20the%20corporate%20ladder%3F%20Share%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-no-promotion-manager-stress-pay-work-life-balance-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700735521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd16322cf74a5739a75cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-no-promotion-manager-stress-pay-work-life-balance-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20millennials%20don't%20want%20to%20become%20managers%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20added%20work%20involved%2C%20but%20that%20could%20create%20a%20succession%20gap%20at%20companies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-no-promotion-manager-stress-pay-work-life-balance-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Strike%20kills%20actress%20performing%20to%20Russian%20troops%20in%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A